FAS (MW~ 270 kD) typically elutes at 0.25 M KCl in three 0.5 ml fractions identified using 4-15% SDS-PAGE with Coomassie G250 stain (Bio-Rad).
Each well contains 2 µg purified FAS, 100 mM K<sub>2</sub>HPO<sub>4</sub>, pH 6.5, 1 mM dithiothreitol (Sigma), and. 187.5 µM β-NADPH (Sigma).
Stock solutions of inhibitors are prepared in DMSO at 2, 1, and 0.5 mg/ml resulting in final concentrations of 20, 10, and 5 µg/ml when 1 µl of stock is added per well.
